
                                            The NUM has announced its members will go on strike from next week Sunday, demanding a once off payment of R1,100 and an increase of 8% next year
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) says the planned strike by its workers will run indefinitely until its demands are met  The NUM has announced its members will go on strike from next week Sunday, demanding a once off payment of R1,100 and an increase of 8% next year But the larger companies are offering an increase of R1,100 for year one for lower paid workers and a 7.5% increase for higher categories. While smaller companies have offered increases ranging between 5% and 7%  The union’s Livhuwani Mamburu said, “The NUM will demand 9,5% increase in the third year.”